"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-news-2024-0914-1470026-funeral-of-ugandan-olympian-takes-place\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Olympian Rebecca Cheptegei, who died earlier this month after her partner set her on fire, has been buried in Uganda.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 8, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999591299281898, \"rank\": 3.936603763619043e-05, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 9, \"end\": 16, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca\", \"score\": 0.6079709667259847, \"rank\": 0.6448153840362194, \"text\": \"Rebecca\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca\"}, {\"begin\": 110, \"end\": 116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.988591495812545e-24, \"text\": \"Uganda\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dickson Ndiema Marangach, 32, assaulted Ms Cheptegei in her home in Endebess near the Ugandan border on 1 September.\", \"from\": 119, \"to\": 235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 119, \"end\": 126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Dickson\", \"score\": 0.8997266130358252, \"rank\": 0.07249797265269027, \"text\": \"Dickson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Dickson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_Dickson\"}, {\"begin\": 187, \"end\": 195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Endebess\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Endebess\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Endebess\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Endebess\"}, {\"begin\": 205, \"end\": 212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2671303485741096e-17, \"text\": \"Ugandan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 33-year-old, who debuted this summer in the women's marathon at the Paris Olympics, died as a result of severe burns.\", \"from\": 237, \"to\": 358, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The brutal assault shocked the East African region and prompted a global outpouring of tributes, with activists condemning another act of gender-based violence.\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 520, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms Cheptegei's family say the couple had argued over ownership of the property where she lived with her sister and daughters.\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her attacker later died from injuries sustained in the assault.\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 711, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is the latest incident of gender-based violence in Kenya.\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 773, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 767, \"end\": 772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.432421856042205e-19, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rain fell as the athlete's body crossed the Kenya-Uganda border late yesterday afternoon ahead of the funeral in the family's village of Bukwo, some 380km northeast of Uganda's capital Kampala.\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 912, \"end\": 917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukwo\", \"score\": 0.9999996202189589, \"rank\": 3.797812894746916e-07, \"text\": \"Bukwo\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukwo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukwo\"}, {\"begin\": 943, \"end\": 949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.988591495812545e-24, \"text\": \"Uganda\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\"}, {\"begin\": 960, \"end\": 967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kampala\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5037703492329342e-20, \"text\": \"Kampala\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kampala\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kampala\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are extremely saddened,\\\" said her estranged husband Simon Ayeko, with whom she had two daughters.\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 1071, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As a father it has been very difficult,\\\" he said, explaining he had not been able to break the news to their children.\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Slowly we will tell them the truth.\\\"\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1231, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms Cheptegei, a sergeant in the Uganda Peoples' Defence Forces, was buried with military honours, Beatrice Ayikoru, Uganda's Olympics Committee secretary general and part of the burial organising committee, said.\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1445, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1265, \"end\": 1271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.988591495812545e-24, \"text\": \"Uganda\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\"}, {\"begin\": 1281, \"end\": 1295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finnish_Defence_Forces\", \"score\": 0.9993155268492591, \"rank\": 0.000684941975117346, \"text\": \"Defence Forces\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finnish_Defence_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finnish_Defence_Forces\"}, {\"begin\": 1331, \"end\": 1339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_d'Este\", \"score\": 0.6063379662432404, \"rank\": 0.6489789063918022, \"text\": \"Beatrice\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_d'Este\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_d'Este\"}, {\"begin\": 1349, \"end\": 1355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.988591495812545e-24, \"text\": \"Uganda\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uganda\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Scores of athletes travelled to the small village to attend.\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She greatly contributed to the promotion of athletics until her last days,\\\" coach Alex Malinga, who trained her as a teenager, said.\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1592, \"end\": 1604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Malinga\", \"score\": 0.9999872138488426, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Malinga\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Malinga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Malinga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Local media say Ms Cheptegei's daughters witnessed the attack.\", \"from\": 1644, \"to\": 1706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Police said Marangach snuck into her home while she was at church with her children.\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think at that time, their relationship had become sour,\\\" Ms Cheptegei's brother-in-law, Moses Kipsiro, said.\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1904, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I did not know then something was wrong,\\\" said Mr Kipsiro, who previously trained with Ms Cheptegei and also hails from Bukwo.\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 2033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2027, \"end\": 2032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukwo\", \"score\": 0.9999996202189589, \"rank\": 3.797812894746916e-07, \"text\": \"Bukwo\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukwo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukwo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The vicious assault has thrown yet another spotlight on what activists have called a femicide epidemic.Kenya reported 725 femicide cases in 2022 alone, according to the latest UN figures.\", \"from\": 2035, \"to\": 2222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2211, \"end\": 2213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"score\": 0.9949019249525766, \"rank\": 0.004390456868197167, \"text\": \"UN\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A report the following year by Kenya's National Bureau of Statistics found 34 percent of women had experienced physical violence since the age of 15.\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2255, \"end\": 2260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.432421856042205e-19, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At least two other athletes, Agnes Tirop and Damaris Mutua, have lost their lives in domestic violence incidents since 2021.\", \"from\": 2375, \"to\": 2499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2420, \"end\": 2427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damaris_(biblical_figure)\", \"score\": 0.9999999689825931, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Damaris\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damaris_(biblical_figure)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damaris_(biblical_figure)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Source:AFP    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026.\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9irea